---SECURITY INCIDENT REPORT---

Incident ID: 320
Reported By: Braulio Garcia - Tier 1 SOC Analyst 
Date: February 18, 2026
Time Detected: 13:07 PST
Severity: High
Status: Escalated to Tier 2
Attack Technique: Remote Code Execution (RCE)


1. Executive Summary
  
  A CVE-2025-53770 (SharePoint ToolShell RCE) alert was triggered at 13:07 PM involving inbound HTTP traffic from a suspicious external IP 107.191.58.76. Web logs showed a suspicious POST request to a sensitive endpoint with a large payload.

Threat intelligence lookup identified the source IP as associated with CVE-2025-53770 exploitation activity.

Endpoint investigation confirmed successful remote code execution and evidence of post-exploitation activity including, web shell deployment and successful execution of obsfucated PowerShell commands.

Based on the observed IOC's and confirmed execution of malicious activity, it was concluded that the web server was compromised. 

Incident escalated to Tier 2. Immediate containment of the affected server was recommended.


2. Detection Summary

    Alert Source: SIEM Correlation Rule - Web Attack Detection
    Rule Triggered: CVE‑225‑53770 SharePoint ToolShell Auth Bypass and RCE
    Initial Indicator: Inbound HTTP POST to '/_layouts/15/ToolPane.aspx?DisplayMode=Edit'

3. Timeline of Events 

  Time (PST)           Event
  13:07                SIEM triggered an RCE detection alert 
  13:08                Web logs inspected, finding POST request with large payload from an unusual host IP 
  13:11                Email Security tool checked, ensuring the request was not part of an authorized penetration test by the organization
